<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🎮 M000 Pre-Lesson — Get Comfy in Minecraft</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Moving &amp; Building · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Time:</strong> about 15 minutes</p>
<hr />
<p>A quick warm-up <strong>before Lesson 1</strong>. No coding. Just get comfortable moving around and building on your tablet. Open your Minecraft world and play.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Move Around 🎮</h2>
<p>Try each one. Tick the box when you can do it.</p>
<ul>
<li>☐ Walk</li>
<li>☐ Look around</li>
<li>☐ Jump</li>
<li>☐ Tap to place a block</li>
<li>☐ Hold to break a block</li>
</ul>
<blockquote>
<p>On a tablet: move with the <strong>left thumb pad</strong>, look by <strong>dragging the right side</strong>, <strong>tap</strong> to place a block, <strong>hold</strong> to break one.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>2 · Build a House 🏠</h2>
<p>Build a small house. Any size is fine. It needs <strong>3 things</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>☐ Walls (use any block)</li>
<li>☐ A door</li>
<li>☐ A window (use a <strong>glass pane</strong>)</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>3 · Send It 📸</h2>
<p>Take a photo of your house and send it to your teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
